When the planting of a permit area is completed, the permittee shall file a planting report with the cabinet on a form to be prescribed and furnished by the cabinet, giving the following information:
Identification of the operation;
The type of planting or seeding, including mixtures and amounts;
The date of planting or seeding;
The area of land planted;
Other relevant information, including whether the operator has utilized a pollinator colony, as the cabinet may require.
